/* STDLIB/corpus/2487_xii_lattice_live.iii
 *
 * XII @lattice -- LIVE (independence-closure Phase E; discharges basal-census breach #1).
 *
 * Before this program NO source in the tree carried @lattice, so cg_r3.iii's XII gate
 * (cg_r3.iii:3574 -- `sema_xii_anno_has_in_ast(...LATTICE)`) was NEVER taken: a dead branch,
 * flagged by the systems-map audit and pinned as an island breach.  This program carries
 * @lattice on `latwork`, so compiling it DRIVES the whole XII codegen pipeline:
 *   r3_pe_canonicalise -> r3_compute_circ -> r3_pe_lattice_emit
 * which emits, INSTEAD of the legacy block, a multi-byte-NOP LDIL placeholder into .text plus
 * a 24-byte call-site descriptor into the `.iii_xii_calls` section (the LDIL fill target).
 *
 * COMPILE-TIME proof (xii_live_gate.sh): the compiled .o.s contains `.section .iii_xii_calls`
 * with a non-empty descriptor AND the @lattice fn's body is the NOP placeholder, not `x+1`.
 * RUN proof: main ignores latwork's (placeholder) result and returns the sentinel 99, so the
 * program links + runs sovereignly -- the XII branch is exercised without the program's exit
